cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.MM

The paper deals with generative models for natural images and their use in solving inverse problems such as image restoration and compressive sensing. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also introduces a new method for reducing the representation error of GAN priors, which involves modeling images as the linear combination of a GAN prior with a Deep Decoder. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on image superresolution, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
